<subSubSection id="FEBB0CFCAD09FFA4FF2BA88EFCF25F9D" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="B61E5F77AD09FFA4FF2BA88EFCF25F9D" blockId="6.[151,1436,1934,2038]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis id="84D58365AD09FFA4FF2BA88EFEA85FC3" bold="true" box="[198,326,1934,1960]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Antenna 1 peduncle with 3 distinct articles, article 3 short. Lateral cephalic lobes subacute and slightly downward-pointing. Eyes apparently absent. Pereopod 3 propodus largely expanded and strongly subchelate. Pereopod 7 posteroventral margin truncate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
