<subSubSection id="FEBB0CFCAD08FFABFF2BA82EFE605C6F" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="10" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="description">
<paragraph id="B61E5F77AD08FFABFF2BA82EFBF0594D" blockId="7.[151,1436,1838,2019]" lastBlockId="9.[151,1436,152,1492]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="10" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis id="84D58365AD08FFA5FF2BA82EFE195F23" bold="true" box="[198,503,1838,1864]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Description of 
<typeStatus id="691AE1D5AD08FFA5FE68A82EFE1D5F23" box="[389,499,1838,1864]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
Antenna 1 subequal to antenna 2; peduncle with 3 distinct articles, article 3 short and telescoped into article 2; flagellum 6+ articulate, article 1 slightly longer than article 2; accessory flagellum 3-articulate. Antenna 2 less than 40% of body length; flagellum 6-articulate. Calceoli absent. Eyes apparently absent. Lateral cephalic lobes subacute, narrowly rounded apically and slightly downwardpointing. Epistome and upper lip fused. Mandible incisor broad, smooth; lacinia mobilis absent from both mandibles; molar a setose flap; palp attached centrally, article 3 greater than half length of article 2. Maxilla 1 outer plate with setal-teeth in a modified 6/5 arrangement; palp present, 2 articulate. Maxilliped palp 4- articulate, article 4 well developed; outer plate poorly developed, not reaching palp article 3, inner margin with 4 or 5 weak robust setae; inner plate about half the length of outer plate.
</paragraph>
